assets.name: assets/eEwYlXDh0Qs
assets.description: Up the street from my house there is a private drive with a sign out front that says Camp Huntington. It’s somewhat of a mysterious street, with a house near the entrance with a couple roosters – an unusual sight and sound in Los Angeles. If you pull up the drive a little bit you find this dilapitated log cabin. I suspect it must have some historical significance, otherwise why would it still be left standing, perhaps this was property once owned by Mr Huntington himself. Who knows. I captured this using the new LiDAR iPad using the Polycam app. Learn more at: https://polycam.ai/
